U.S. Cl. 382--189 15 Claims
OG exemplary drawing
1.
A method for handwriting recognition, comprising the steps of:
displaying a graphical image having at least one handwriting entry area to receive handwritten input;
processing information representing the handwritten input with a selected set comprising a plurality of dictionaries having stored recognition data to identify candidate recognition information, the selected set of the plurality of dictionaries being selected automatically in response to receiving the handwritten input in a particular handwriting entry area; and
displaying the candidate recognition information.
